WORK SUMMARY :
A task was given  to developed a simple Mood Tracker application using React.js where users can select their current mood (such as happy, sad, excited, or tired).
Implemented React state management using the use State hook to dynamically update the UI based on the selected mood. 
Applied event handling and conditional rendering to change the interface in real time whenever the user selects a different mood.

LEARNING OUTCOMES :
The Assignment was helpful to understood the concept of state management in React using the use State hook , 
conditional rendering to update UI dynamically based on user input.
Improved understanding of component-based architecture and interactive UI design in React.
